CatDescriptText: Mrs. Fannie Moncrief, housewife, Beltzhoover, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, August 26, 1961, pg. 1 with question: "Do you think there will be war over Berlin?"  Answer reads: "I don't think so.  There will be a meeting of the minds and they will reach some sort of an agreement."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Fannie Moncrief wearing lattice patterned shirt, beaded necklace, eyeglasses, and hair net, standing in front of building, another version; Blurred view, possibly buildings
